    "Let us discuss a special class of 3-charges which exhibit both invertible and non-invertible 1-form symmetry fractionalization.",
    "An irreducible 3-charge in this class exhibits the following physical properties: 1.",
    "The localized symmetries on a 3-dimensional operator O 3 furnishing the 3-charge are captured essentially by topological line operators living on O 3.",
    "These line operators can not only have non-invertible fusion rules, but also can braid non-trivially with each other.",
    "These line operators and their properties are encoded mathematically in the structure of a braided fusion category B."
